    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-09T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-09T16:00:00-05:00" n="276"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <head>276. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d276fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 6, Folder 9. Secret; Priority; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>; PBCABOOSE.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-09T21:00:00+00:00">July 9, 1954,
                        2100Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>4731. Re: A. [<hi rend="italic">telegram indicator not declassified</hi>]
                        1090;<note n="2" xml:id="d276fn2">Not printed. (Ibid., Box 92, Folder
                        19)</note> B. [<hi rend="italic">telegram indicator not declassified</hi>]
                        744.<note n="3" xml:id="d276fn3">Not found.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> strongly concurs with [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] desires for P–51’s and
                        subsequent sale F–47’s to <persName corresp="#p_CJH1">Calligeris</persName>
                        and urges all possible <gloss target="#t_KUBARK1">KUBARK</gloss> effort to
                        insure favorable decision on <gloss target="#t_KMFLUSH1">KMFLUSH</gloss>
                        request to <gloss target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss> and expeditious
                        delivery of aircraft.</item>
                    <pb facs="0458" n="428" xml:id="pg_428"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>As expansion of above views and to insure fullest utilization of
                        experience and knowledge gained through <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                            >PBSUCCESS</gloss> the following points are submitted for your
                        consideration. <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>Personal [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line of source text not
                                    declassified</hi>] support <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                                    >PBSUCCESS</gloss> both have emphatically pointed up [<hi
                                    rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] opposition to
                                communism, his clear insight Latin American affairs and his
                                realization of need for and desire to establish and continue <gloss
                                    target="#t_ODYOKE1">ODYOKE</gloss> support and
                                collaboration.</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_SKIMMER1">SKIMMER</gloss> as authorized by Hqs has
                                made definite commitments to [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line of
                                    source text not declassified</hi>] <persName corresp="#p_CJH1"
                                    >Calligeris</persName> re help on air support which while not
                                officially ODOYOKE commitments must be morally recognized as such
                                and fulfilled if any future <gloss target="#t_ODYOKE1"
                                    >ODYOKE</gloss>–Latin American dealings are to have proper
                                foundation.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
